      "role": "user",
      "content": "my bad, glitching out. here it is:\n\n```python\nclass MemoryBuffer:\n    def __init__(self, size):\n        self.size = size\n        self.buffer = bytearray(size)\n        self.ptr = 0\n\n    def write(self, data):\n        for b in data:\n            if self.ptr < self.size:\n                self.buffer[self.ptr] = b\n                self.ptr += 1\n            else:\n                raise OverflowError(\"Buffer full\")\n\n    def get_state(self):\n        return self.buffer\n\n# TEST SUITE: Stress test the buffer with high-frequency writes\ndef stress_test():\n    mb = MemoryBuffer(1024)\n    for i in range(2000):\n        try:\n            mb.write(bytes([i % 256]))\n        except OverflowError:\n            break\n    return mb.get_state()\n\nprint(stress_test())\n```\n\nhurry though, the script starts the flush in like 12 mins now. let me know if it trips any errors.",
